article.linkText: Robinson's 25 points lead NJIT over Delaware State 81-72
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- — Sebastian Robinson's 25 points helped NJIT defeat Delaware State 81-72 on Monday night. Robinson also contributed five assists for the Highlanders (1-3). Adam Hess scored 14 points and added nine rebounds. Levi Lawal had 14 points and shot 4 of 4 from the field and 6 for 8 from the line. The Hornets (1-4) were led by Martez Robinson, who recorded 21 points and six rebounds. Jevin Muniz added 18 points and three steals for Delaware State. In addition, Alston Andrews finished with 12 points and 10 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
